  <title>Resource Unique Identifier</title>
  <para>
    The unique identifier resource includes generating, registering and deleting unique identifiers.
  </para>
  <caution>
    <title>Authorization</title>
    <para>
      Any access to any method provided by this resource <emphasis role="strong">MUST</emphasis> be authorized by an access token.
    </para>
    <para>
      See <link linkend='uid-arch-token'>Authentication for the REST API</link>.
    </para>
  </caution>
  <para>
    You can use the UID Generator Service API to perform the following operations:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist mark='bullet'>
    <listitem>
      <link linkend='uid-search'>Search for Unique Identifiers</link>
      <para/>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <link linkend='uid-lookup'>Lookup an Unique Identifiers</link>
      <para/>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <link linkend='uid-create'>Generate an Unique Identifier</link>
      <para/>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <link linkend='uid-modify'>Register an Unique Identifier</link>
      <para/>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <link linkend='uid-delete'>Delete an Unique Identifier</link>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
